9. MAIN API REQUIREMENTS
==================================================
Implement these REST endpoints.

A. Send notification manually
POST /api/notifications/send

Request:
- recipientUserId
- channel
- type
- templateCode optional
- subject optional
- title optional
- message optional
- relatedEntityType optional
- relatedEntityId optional
- variables map optional

Behavior:
1. resolve recipient contact data from User Service if needed
2. render message from template if templateCode exists
3. create notification with PENDING
4. send via selected strategy
5. update status to SENT / FAILED
6. return saved notification

B. Send booking event notification
POST /api/notifications/events/booking

Request example:
- rentalId
- eventType (BOOKING_REQUESTED, BOOKING_APPROVED, BOOKING_REJECTED, RENTAL_STARTED, RENTAL_COMPLETED)
- channel optional
- notifyOwner boolean
- notifyRenter boolean

Behavior:
- fetch rental data
- fetch owner/renter contact profiles
- build variables
- send notifications to relevant participants

C. Send payment event notification
POST /api/notifications/events/payment

Request example:
- rentalId
- eventType (PAYMENT_PENDING, PAYMENT_CONFIRMED, ESCROW_RELEASED, DISPUTE_OPENED)
- channel optional
- notifyOwner boolean
- notifyRenter boolean

Behavior:
- fetch rental snapshot and/or payment snapshot
- send notifications to relevant users

D. Get notifications by user
GET /api/notifications/user/{userId}

Optional query params:
- status
- channel
- unreadOnly
- page
- size

E. Mark notification as read
PATCH /api/notifications/{notificationId}/read

F. Create communication message
POST /api/communications

Request:
- rentalId optional
- senderUserId
- receiverUserId
- message
- messageType

G. Get communication messages for rental
GET /api/communications/rental/{rentalId}

H. Mark communication message as read
PATCH /api/communications/{messageId}/read

I. Create/update notification template
POST /api/notifications/templates
PUT /api/notifications/templates/{templateId}

J. Get all templates
GET /api/notifications/templates

